HEADWORD: Landtrost
<hw>Landtrost</hw></mhw>. <ety>[D., fr. <ets>land</ets> land +
<ets>drost</ets> a kind of official; akin to G.
<ets>truchsess</ets>.]</ety> <mark>(In South Africa)</mark> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A chief magistrate in rural districts. He was replaced in 1827 by
⟦ldquo⟧resident magistrates.⟦rdquo⟧</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The
president of the Heemraad.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

